stories.text: Join an Amotions workshop on developing emotional intelligence, which is crucial for professional and personal success, by Dr. David Caruso, co-author of the Meyer, Salovey, Caruso Emotional Intelligence test, and The Emotionally Intelligent Manager, and research affiliate at Yale today on Dec 9. Get expert assessments, high-quality content, exercises, and AI insights on Amotions to develop soft skills, and join a supportive community of peers, coaches, and industry leaders. See a preview of the workshop and register here: https://amotionsinc.com/

stories.text: I’m spending some time in Bologna, and one thing I noticed is that while the data you get for you cell phone is very fast (many people don’t bother to use wifi) GPS feels noticeably less precise. I can’t be imagining this can I? In Mexico/USA it’s usually very accurate, but here sometimes off by a block or two…
stories.title: Ask HN: Consumer GPS is not as precise in Italy as North America?
